latestPosts.caption:
Had an amazing time at Hakman’s Hotel in Mussoorie! 💛
Truly impressed by the warm hospitality and the prime location of the property — just a walk away from some of Mussoorie’s top spots! 🌄✨

📍Nearby Attractions:
🔸 Gun Hill – for that classic cable car ride & panoramic views 🎡
🔸 Mall Road – shop, stroll & soak in the vibes 🛍️
🔸 Camel’s Back Road – peaceful walks with scenic views 🐪
🔸 Christ Church – a beautiful touch of colonial charm ⛪
🔸 Lal Tibba – highest point for sunrise lovers 🌅

Swipe through to see moments from this memorable stay! 📸

Explored the quiet charm of Landour.

The serene vibe and stunning architecture of Landour Church — a peaceful pause and some of my favorite clicks from the trip.

Started the day at Chaar Dukaan — the pancakes at Heart of Landour truly lived up to the name.
(Tried : Chocolate Fantasy with ice cream pancake 🥞) 

Tried Landour Bakehouse too. Had beautiful setting, but honestly didn’t feel it lived up to the hype.Picked up some fresh homemade breads, cinnamon buns, and a jar of jam to carry a piece of the hills back home.

A slow day well spent in the hills. ⛰️
.
.
.
